archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: Azure services (as a Product)
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation: A cartography of the Azure services as a Product, i.e. something produced by Microsoft and related to its business, i.e. what Microsfot sells to a Business client. This view aims at being used when dealing with business aspect, i.e. what are the service consummed and payed by an organization. It can also be used for comparing commercial offers with other cloud services providers such as AWS or Google. It is closely related to the technical view of the Microsoft Services as enacted for consummers, or as realization of applications used by organisations. The cartography was initiated from Azure Plant UML at https://github.com/RicardoNiepel/Azure-PlantUML/blob/master/AzureSymbols.md#azure-symbols. Then it has been continuously updated capturing evolution of Microsoft Services or completing the cartography with missing services.
